House Resolution 908
By: Representative Burns of the 159th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Ella Levenia Sosebee McMichen; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Ella Levenia Sosebee McMichen on March 24, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Ella Levenia Sosebee McMichen was born on June 30, 1930, as the 12th child
5 of William Lawrence Sosebee and Ollie Ledford Edison Sosebee; and
6 WHEREAS, she was united in love and marriage to her husband, Orlando "Pete" McMichen,
7 and was blessed with four remarkable children, Aurelia, Charlotte, Joyce, and Kenneth; five
8 wonderful grandchildren, Jana, Stephenie, Kristy, Justin, and Kaleb; nine beloved
9 great-grandchildren; and six magnificent great-great-grandchildren; and
10 WHEREAS, a devoted homemaker, she dedicated herself to raising her children and
11 embraced her role as a loving Nanny to her grandchildren, great-grandchildren, and
12 great-great-grandchildren; and
