13 WHEREAS, a proud graduate of Dallas High School in 1948, Ella Levenia Sosebee
14 McMichen remained actively connected with her classmates through reunions and events
15 with the 48 Gang; and
16 WHEREAS, in her later years, she enjoyed traveling and playing cards, but above all, she
17 loved Jesus and remained a faithful prayer warrior, lifting up her family and friends in
18 constant prayer; and
19 WHEREAS, she gave inspiration to many through her high ideals, morals, and deep concern
20 for her fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding she demonstrated to
21 her family and friends were admired by others; and
22 WHEREAS, she was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
23 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example she made of her life,
24 she made this world a better place in which to live; and
25 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous woman, Ella Levenia Sosebee McMichen will
26 long be remembered for her love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed
27 by all who had the great fortune of knowing her.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Ella Levenia Sosebee
30 McMichen and express their deepest and most sincere regret at her passing.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
33 family of Ella Levenia Sosebee McMichen.
